  "prompt": "What are some recipes using 4 ounces of steak?",
  "response": "Okay, 4 ounces of steak is a small portion, but it's perfect for a quick and flavorful meal.  Here are some recipe ideas using that amount, focusing on pairing it with other ingredients to make a complete and satisfying dish:\n\n**Quick & Easy Options:**\n\n1.  **Steak Bites & Veggies:**\n\n    *   **Concept:**  Cube the steak and quickly sear it with veggies for a one-pan meal.\n    *   **Ingredients:**\n        *   4 oz Steak (sirloin, flank, or tenderloin work well)\n        *   1 tbsp Olive Oil\n        *   1/2 cup Bell Pepper (diced)\n        *   1/2 cup Onion (diced)\n        *   1/2 cup Broccoli florets\n        *   Salt & Pepper to taste\n        *   Optional: Garlic powder, onion powder, red pepper flakes, soy sauce, worcestershire sauce.\n    *   **Instructions:**\n        1.  Cut steak into bite-sized pieces.\n        2.  Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.\n        3.  Add steak and sear quickly on all sides until browned but still tender.  Don't overcook!\n        4.  Add bell pepper, onion, and broccoli.  Saut\u00e9 until vegetables are tender-crisp.\n        5.  Season with salt, pepper, and any other desired spices or sauces.\n        6. Serve immediately\n\n2.  **Steak & Egg Scramble:**\n\n    *   **Concept:** Add protein to a hearty scramble\n    *   **Ingredients:**\n        *   4 oz Steak\n        *   2 Eggs\n        *   1 tbsp Milk or Cream (optional)\n        *   1 tbsp Butter\n        *   Salt & Pepper to taste\n        *   Optional:  Shredded cheese, diced tomatoes, chopped green onions\n    *   **Instructions:**\n        1.  Cook the steak to your liking (sear, pan-fry, or grill). Let it rest for a moment and then dice.\n        2.  Whisk eggs with milk/cream (if using), salt, and pepper.\n        3.  Melt butter in a skillet over medium heat.\n        4.  Pour in the egg mixture and cook, stirring gently, until the eggs are set but still slightly moist.\n        5.  Stir in the diced steak, cheese (if using), and any other desired toppings.\n        6. Serve immediately.\n\n3.  **Steak Salad Topping:**\n\n    *   **Concept:** Make a basic green salad more exciting.\n    *   **Ingredients:**\n        *   4 oz Steak\n        *   Mixed Greens\n        *   Cherry Tomatoes (halved)\n        *   Cucumber (sliced)\n        *   Red Onion (thinly sliced)\n        *   Your favorite Salad Dressing\n        *   Optional:  Crumbled cheese (feta, blue cheese), croutons, avocado\n    *   **Instructions:**\n        1.  Cook the steak to your liking. Let it rest for a moment, then slice thinly against the grain.\n        2.  Combine mixed greens, tomatoes, cucumber, and red onion in a bowl.\n        3.  Top with sliced steak and your favorite salad dressing.\n\n**More Involved (but still quick) Options:**\n\n4.  **Steak & Cheese Quesadilla:**\n\n    *   **Concept:** Upgrade a classic quesadilla.\n    *   **Ingredients:**\n        *   4 oz Steak\n        *   2 Flour Tortillas\n        *   1/2 cup Shredded Cheese (Monterey Jack, Cheddar, or a blend)\n        *   1/4 Onion, thinly sliced and sauteed\n        *   1 tbsp Butter or Oil\n        *   Optional:  Salsa, sour cream, guacamole for serving\n    *   **Instructions:**\n        1.  Cook steak to desired doneness, rest, and slice thinly.\n        2.  Sautee onions until softened and lightly browned\n        3.  Spread cheese over one tortilla.  Top with steak slices and sauteed onions\n        4.  Top with the other tortilla.\n        5.  Melt butter/oil in a skillet over medium heat.\n        6.  Cook the quesadilla for 2-3 minutes per side, or until golden brown and the cheese is melted.\n        7.  Cut into wedges and serve with salsa, sour cream, or guacamole.\n\n5.  **Steak Stir-Fry with Noodles:**\n\n    *   **Concept:**  A simple stir-fry for one person.\n    *   **Ingredients:**\n        *   4 oz Steak\n        *   1 tbsp Soy Sauce\n        *   1 tsp Cornstarch\n        *   1 tsp Sesame Oil\n        *   1/2 cup Stir-Fry Vegetables (broccoli, carrots, snow peas, etc.)\n        *   1/4 cup Cooked Noodles (ramen, udon, or spaghetti)\n        *   Optional:  Ginger, garlic, red pepper flakes\n    *   **Instructions:**\n        1.  Slice steak thinly against the grain.\n        2.  In a small bowl, mix soy sauce, cornstarch, and sesame oil.  Add grated ginger and garlic if using. Marinate steak in this mixture for 5-10 minutes (optional).\n        3.  Heat a wok or large skillet over high heat.\n        4.  Add the steak (and marinade) and stir-fry quickly until browned.\n        5.  Add stir-fry vegetables and cook until tender-crisp.\n        6.  Add cooked noodles and toss to combine.\n        7.  Serve immediately.\n\n6.  **Steak Tacos (Single Serving):**\n\n    *   **Concept:** Two small tacos.\n    *   **Ingredients:**\n        *   4 oz Steak\n        *   2 Small Corn or Flour Tortillas\n        *   Your favorite taco toppings: shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, shredded cheese, salsa, sour cream, cilantro, lime wedges\n        *   Taco seasoning (optional)\n    *   **Instructions:**\n        1.  Cook steak and slice into thin strips. Sprinkle with taco seasoning, if using.\n        2.  Warm tortillas.\n        3.  Fill each tortilla with steak and your desired toppings.\n        4.  Serve immediately.\n\n**Tips for Cooking 4 oz of Steak:**\n\n*   **Choose the right cut:** Tenderloin, sirloin, or flank steak are good choices that cook quickly.\n*   **High Heat is Key:**  Use high heat and a hot pan (cast iron is ideal) to get a good sear.\n*   **Don't Overcook:**  A small piece of steak will cook quickly. Use a meat thermometer to ensure you don't overcook it. Medium-rare (130-135\u00b0F) is a good target.\n*   **Let it Rest:**  Allow the steak to rest for a few minutes after cooking before slicing. This helps the juices redistribute, resulting in a more tender and flavorful steak.\n\nEnjoy your perfectly portioned steak!  These are just starting points, so feel free to adjust the ingredients and seasonings to your liking.\n",
